{
  "stem": "12494.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My family and I particularly, I-- I felt very warm about him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I trusted everything he'd do.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if he asked for whatever, he would have gotten it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we-- we-- we did go by his word.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And his word was that 600 Jews would be saved as a sign of good will, on the part of him, the highest authority, [INAUDIBLE] that was never mentioned at the time, the part of the highest authorities, despite the fact that Eichmann personally is disgusted with the idea, because he would love to kill all Jews.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But these 600 Jews would go to Palestine with certain conditions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "One, that Hitler did not want to antagonize the Arab peoples, and therefore he would not let Jews go directly to Palestine from Hungary via Romania and Turkey and so forth.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But what he would do is he would transport the Jews to-- to Spain.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And from Spain, if the Jews could arrange via the British and the Zionist authorities to be taken to Palestine, they would be essentially out of the purview of the Germans, and there would be no objection to that.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then negotiations went on, and then the number was increased to 1,200.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From 600 [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the selection process started.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was not in on the selection process, but my father told me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was deeply in it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How was-- how did--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The idea was that 600, the first 600 would be selected on, quote, 'merit,' meaning they would be leaders of the Jewish community who deserved to be saved and their families.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the second 600 would be putting up the money necessary to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to-- that they earn this money for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So the spaces were sold.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
